<br>
Anyone have any experience with this weapon and how good a taunt its proc is?<br>
<br>
-Turek <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uturektoestomper.showPublicProfile?language=EN>TurekToestomper</A> at: 9/12/02 9:09:21 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ubranaelan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Branaelan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/12/02 9:11:20 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3877.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Blinding Poison III</span><hr size=1> This weapon will grab aggro from my experience in your average level 55-60 experience group.  The problem with it however is that the proc is a blind and if the mob is not locked on you it could go running all over the zone blind screaming bloody murder.  At best this can be very annoying, at worst it's a wipeout.  <br>
<br>
For PvP I'd say this weapon would rock, otherwise I'd add it to the list of &quot;cursed&quot; weapons and get rid of it ASAP.<br>
<br>
Branaelan<br>
58 Warrior <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uscarsoulklaw.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ScarSoulKlaw</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 131<br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/12/02 11:19:40 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3877.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Blinding Poison III</span><hr size=1> I used one for a few weeks.  For xp groups where control over distance from the mob wasn't a problem it was fine and the agro was insanely good.  Cleric nukes/heals, Shaman slows/DoTs/heals, Wizard Nukes - no problems after only 1 proc.  I loved this weapon !!!<br>
<br>
I tried it on a raid one night, I was the ST and used it thinking as long as I stayed close to the adds we were fine.  <br>
<br>
As soon as a few people broke max melee distance and pushed me off the mob it was running like mad, summoned me out of the camp and proceeded to get some friends together and dirtnap me.  I sold the WESS the next day.<br>
<br>
Lesson learned - great for small xp groups and dueling.  Don't ever take it out of your bag when things are serious. <p>Scartle SoulKlaw<br>
Dwarven Warlord of Forlorn, E'CI Server<br>
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=69785">Hard work and patience pay off</a> 
